==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Physician
<hw>Phy*si"cian</hw> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧*z⟦icr⟧sh"⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>fisician</ets>, <ets>fisicien</ets>, OF.
<ets>physucien</ets>, a physician, in F., a natural philosopher, an
experimentalist in physics. See <er>Physic</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A person skilled in medicine, or the art of healing; especially,
one trained and licensed to treat illness and prescribe medicines; a
doctor of medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, figuratively, one who ministers to moral
diseases; <as>as, a <ex>physician</ex> of the soul</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Physicianed</ent>⟦br⟧
